__FORCETOC__
'''Andrei Kharlov''' (born on [[November 20]], [[1968]]) is a Russian chess player.  In [[1992]], he recieved the title of [[grandmaster]] after tying for first place in the 1990 [[Russian Chess Championship|Russian National Championships]].<ref>http://www.rebel.nl/kharlov.htm Accomplishments of Grandmaster Andrei Kharlov</ref>  Since then, Kharlov has won the [[1996]] [[Eurocup (chess)|Eurocup]] and the [[1998]] [[Russian Club Cup]] with the [[Kazan]] [[Chess team|chess team]].  In [[2000]], he tied for first in the Russian National Championship in [[Samara, Russia|Samara]] and tied for first in the [[European Individual Chess Championship]] in [[Saint-Vincent, Italy|Saint-Vincent]].<ref>http://www.rebel.nl/kharlov.htm Accomplishments of Grandmaster Andrei Kharlov</ref>

==Notable Games==
===Andrei Kharlov vs Vassily Ivanchuk===
In the [[2005]] [[Aeroflot Open]] Andrei Kharlov played [[Vassily Ivanchuk]] as white.  The game played through the [[Krause Variation]] of the [[Queen's Pawn Game]] opening.'''1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 c5 3. c3 a5 4. dxc5 Nf6 5. c4 e6 6. cxd5 Bxc5 7. Qc2 Bb4+ 8. Bd2 exd5 9. Bxb4 axb4 10. Nbd2 Nc6 11. Nb3 Bg4 12. g3 Rc8 13. Qd1 O-O 14. Bg2 Qb6 15. O-O Rfd8 16. Qd2 h6 17. Rfd1 Ne4 18. Qe1 d4 19. Nc1 Nc5 20. Nd3 Nxd3 21. Rxd3 Ra8 22. Rd2 Ra5 23. Qd1 Be6 24. b3 Bf5 25. h3 Be4 26. Ne1 Bxg2 27. Kxg2 Rc5 28. Nf3 Rc3 29. Qb1 Qa5''' {{Chess diagram small|=
